sentences: Colman Pearce (born 22 September 1938) is an Irish pianist and conductor.

He became a conductor for the RTÉ Concert Orchestra in the late 1960s as well as being musical director for the 1971 Eurovision Song Contest and then conducting the 1972, 1973, 1974 and 1975 Irish entries.
